b'' b'this notice will be posted weekly in sci.space, sci.astro, and' b'sci.space.shuttle.' b'' b'the frequently asked questions (faq) list for sci.space and sci.astro is' b'posted approximately monthly. it also covers many questions that come up on' b'sci.space.shuttle (for shuttle launch dates, see below).' b'' b'the faq is posted with a long expiration date, so a copy may be in your' b'news spool directory (look at old articles in sci.space). if not, here are' b'two ways to get a copy without waiting for the next posting:' b'' b'(1) if your machine is on the internet, it can be obtained by anonymous' b'ftp from the space archive at ames.arc.nasa.gov in directory' b'pub/space/faq.' b'' b'containing the single line:' b'' b'help' b'' b'the archive server will return directions on how to use it. to get an' b'index of files in the faq directory, send email containing the lines:' b'' b'send space faq/index' b'send space faq/faq1' b'' b'use these files as a guide to which other files to retrieve to answer' b'your questions.' b'' b'shuttle launch dates are posted by ken hollis periodically in' b'sci.space.shuttle. a copy of his manifest is now available in the ames' b'archive in pub/space/faq/manifest and may be requested from the email' b"archive-server with 'send space faq/manifest'. please get this document" b'instead of posting requests for information on launches and landings.' b'' b'do not post followups to this article; respond to the author.' 